In article <CFEo8r.Ktt@ns1.nodak.edu> lihke@plains.NoDak.edu (Robert Lihke) writes:
>Couldnt a simple, cheap hardware random number device be made  that
>combined the analog signals of AM radio noise (in a non-AM band) with
>another factor, say, temperature? This should not be TOO expensive.
>
>
You can purchase noise diodes. Most zenner diodes can be used as well. You
don't need to use stray RF pickup. In a random number generator you would
want the noise source to be well screened from RF so that it could not be
tampered with using RF....

Pete.
